@startuml
title Parallel 5-Surface Scanner Execution

participant "Scan Processor" as Processor
participant "ExecutorService" as Executor
participant "DNS Scanner" as DNS
participant "SSL Scanner" as SSL
participant "HTTP Scanner" as HTTP
participant "CT Log Scanner" as CT
participant "Exposure Scanner" as Exposure
participant "Result Aggregator" as Aggregator

Processor -> Executor: 1. Submit 5 parallel tasks

== Task 1: DNS ==
Executor -> DNS: 2. performScan()
activate DNS
DNS -> DNS: 3. Query A, MX, NS, TXT
DNS -> DNS: 4. Check DNSSEC
DNS --> Executor: 5. Return DnsResult
deactivate DNS

== Task 2: SSL ==
Executor -> SSL: 6. performScan()
activate SSL
SSL -> SSL: 7. Connect :443, get cert
SSL -> SSL: 8. Check expiry, weak protocols
SSL --> Executor: 9. Return SslResult
deactivate SSL

== Task 3: HTTP ==
Executor -> HTTP: 10. performScan()
activate HTTP
HTTP -> HTTP: 11. GET / fetch headers
HTTP -> HTTP: 12. Check HSTS, CSP, XFO
HTTP -> HTTP: 13. Probe sensitive paths
HTTP --> Executor: 14. Return HttpResult
deactivate HTTP

== Task 4: CT Logs ==
Executor -> CT: 15. performScan()
activate CT
CT -> CT: 16. Query crt.sh API
CT -> CT: 17. Parse subdomains
CT --> Executor: 18. Return CtResult
deactivate CT

== Task 5: Exposures ==
Executor -> Exposure: 19. performScan()
activate Exposure
Exposure -> Exposure: 20. Directory listing check
Exposure -> Exposure: 21. Backup file probes
Exposure --> Executor: 22. Return ExposureResult
deactivate Exposure

== Aggregate ==
Executor -> Executor: 23. allOf().join()
Executor -> Aggregator: 24. Merge 5 results
Aggregator --> Processor: 25. Return aggregated JSON

@enduml